         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [Minchin Jas. Can 4 days sick be counted as annual leave?]...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.06.12a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Patterson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 4373, vol. 1894 X, VPRS 1168/P inward correspondence registers, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: start; hyphenation-ladder-count: no-limit; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; hyphenation-remain-char-count: 2; hyphenation-push-char-count: 2; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: start; hyphenation-ladder-count: no-limit; font-family: Geneva; hyphenate: false; hyphenation-remain-char-count: 2; hyphenation-push-char-count: 2; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found; item is a register entry only, of an item dated 12 June 1894. The entry refers to another letter from M, registered as X5436, that has not been found: ‘Reports absence of J. Minchin from duty without leave’. <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">add cross ref to X4232 – is this the same item? - when it has been transcribed – see fns to 93.03.</seg>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">14b.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Minchin Jas. Can 4 days sick be counted as annual leave?]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: start; hyphenation-ladder-count: no-limit; font-family: Geneva; hyphenate: false; hyphenation-remain-char-count: 2; hyphenation-push-char-count: 2; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">This letter was returned to M on 14 June 1894 minuted: 'In future carry out instruction re reporting absence by Telegraph'. M returned the file on 18 June. M had been instructed on 13 October 1893, ‘Report next absence by telegram’, after reporting an earlier absence of Minchin’s due to ill-health.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: start; hyphenation-ladder-count: no-limit; font-family: Geneva; hyphenate: false; hyphenation-remain-char-count: 2; hyphenation-push-char-count: 2; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Andy’s notes indicate another M LFN occurs in the sequence here which should be transcribed as such once with a cross-ref to the above once a date has been got from PRO.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: start; hyphenation-ladder-count: no-limit; font-family: Geneva; hyphenate: false; hyphenation-remain-char-count: 2; hyphenation-push-char-count: 2; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Y5262 'Reports absence of J. Minchin from duty without leave'.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: start; hyphenation-ladder-count: no-limit; font-family: Geneva; hyphenate: false; hyphenation-remain-char-count: 2; hyphenation-push-char-count: 2; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">x-ref this to 94.07.00 X5436.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
